
npm install -g @angular/cli
-for installing angular cli globally in system

npm install --global @angular/cli@next
-for installing next version of angular

ng version 
-to know that angular cli is installed or not and to know current version of it


ng new projectName
-to create a new project file in angular

ng serve
-to run project on browser


ng g m moduleName
-to create a new module

ng g m moduleName --routing
-to create a new module and you need routing as well

ng g c componentName
-to create a component 

ng g c moduleName/componentName
-to create a component in your specific module

npm i -D typescript@4.4.2
-to install desirable typescript version

ng test
- to start automation testing

json-server --watch db.json
-start json server

npm i --save bootstrap
-to install bootstrap in project
other note for this-apply style in angular "./node_modules/bootstrap/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css"

ng serve --port 4202
-to run application on specific port
